correctness.rationale: Significant schema violations and factual issues. (1) Multiple required fields are null/invalid: processParameters.pressure, nucleationPeriod, filmThickness (required at processParameters) are given with None values instead of QUDT-compliant numbers/units; dosingTime/purgeTime/flowRates are empty arrays; thicknessControl.numberofCycles is None; many optional objects are included but set to None (reactor, plasmaPower, opticalProperties, resistivity, roughness, filmDensity, subthresholdSwing, onOffRatio, filmStability, reproducibility), all violating the schema’s object types. (2) Placeholder strings (“Not Found”) used for carrierGas, substrate, deliveryMethod, safety—these are not traceable scientific values and conflict with the requirement of no empty/placeholder values; carrierGas is also required and should be a real gas or omitted if schema allowed. (3) Supercycle sequence is incorrect: article states one Ga2O3, then one ZnO, followed by n In2O3; extracted subcycleSequence is ['In2O3','Ga2O3','ZnO'] for both processes. Number-of-subcycles (3:1:1 for 311; 6:1:1 for 611) is otherwise correct. (4) Film thickness is missing despite being reported as 6 nm in the article. (5) Carrier density units are wrong by 10^6: article gives 3.1×10^20 and 5.6×10^20 cm^-3; extraction records 3.1e20 and 5.6e20 per m^3 instead of 3.1e26 and 5.6e26 per m^3. (6) Crystallinity set to “amorphous” with characterizationMethod “XPS”; the article does not report phase determination by XPS, so this is not traceable and the method is inappropriate. (7) Film composition is incomplete/ambiguous: only a single percentage (e.g., 18.23%) is given without specifying the element; Table 1 provides full In/Ga/Zn/O at.% values which are not fully captured. (8) Several fields that are irrelevant for TALD (plasmaPower) are included with None instead of being omitted. (9) Minor: subthreshold swing was said to be extracted in the paper, but the extraction sets it to None instead of a value (or omitting it); uniformity/conformality left as None despite qualitative evidence of conformal coating. Corrections needed: populate filmThickness (6 nm); fix carrier density units; correct subcycleSequence to ['Ga2O3','ZnO','In2O3']; remove None/placeholder fields or replace with valid, traceable values (e.g., purgingGas=N2 is correct; carrierGas not reported); provide QUDT-compliant pressure or omit if schema allowed; correct crystallinity or remove if not supported; and complete the elemental composition using Table 1 with clear element labels.

completeness.rationale: The extraction is largely incomplete and has several schema and factual issues. (1) Missing processes: The article reports five IGZO ALD supercycle recipes (311, 411, 511, 611, 911) and device/film data for 311, 611, and 911, but only two processes (311 and 611) are extracted. At minimum, a third process for 911 should be included; ideally all five film processes. (2) Required parameters omitted or filled with null/placeholders that violate the schema/requirements: processParameters.pressure (null), substrate ('Not Found' instead of the described etched MIM Mo/SiO2/Mo vertical structure), reactor and plasmaPower set to null (should be omitted if unknown), thicknessControl.numberofCycles (null) and processParameters.filmThickness (null, although the article states 6 nm IGZO channel), materialProperties.uniformity.variation (null), conformality.aspectRatio (null), roughness (null), filmDensity (null), and reactantSelection.carrierGas ('Not Found'). DosingTime, purgeTime, and flowRates are present as empty arrays, which does not meet the no-empty-values requirement. (3) Factual inconsistencies: supercycleDesign.subcycleSequence is incorrect; the article states the sequence is Ga2O3 → ZnO → n×In2O3, not In2O3 → Ga2O3 → ZnO. Carrier density units are wrong: values from Fig. 4 are reported in cm^-3 (e.g., 3.1×10^20 cm^-3 and 5.6×10^20 cm^-3) but were entered with unit PER-M3 without conversion (should be ~3.1×10^26 and 5.6×10^26 m^-3 if using PER-M3). (4) Questionable/unsupported entries: crystallinity marked as amorphous with characterizationMethod = XPS is not supported by the text; no explicit phase analysis method is provided. (5) Partially captured properties: GPC values and precursors/oxidant are correct and traceable, but the film composition is only partially captured (single at.% value) and does not reflect the full table; device metrics for SS and ION/IOFF are omitted though referenced in Fig. 6. To improve completeness, add the missing processes (especially 911), correct the supercycle sequence, populate filmThickness (6 nm), provide or omit (not null) required fields per schema, convert carrier density to PER-M3, and add substrate description, as well as any available SS/ION/IOFF values and resistivity if extractable from the figures.
